               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-842" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-842" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-842" type="surname" value="IVES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-842" type="given" value="EDMUND"></interp>EDMUND IVES</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at No. 124, High Holborn, and am an upholsterer. About half-past twelve o'clock, on the 14th of August, the prisoner came to my shop—he stood still half a minute, then retired, and went and held a conversation with a young man—he came back, in about three minutes, and took a glass out of my shop—I pursued after him—he set the glass down and ran away—I pursued, and called "Stop thief"—this is my glass.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I suppose you are sure of his person? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I was in the counting-house, and saw it.</p>
